# Staging Environment Configuration Template

This file documents the environment variables needed for the staging deployment on Render.

## How to Use

1. Copy this file to Render Dashboard → Environment
2. Replace placeholder values with actual credentials
3. Render will restart the app automatically after saving

## Variables

```ini
APP_NAME="Bayanihan One Window"
APP_ENV=staging
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_URL=https://bayanihan-staging.onrender.com

# Database (Supabase Staging)
DB_CONNECTION=pgsql
DB_HOST=aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com
DB_PORT=5432
DB_DATABASE=postgres
DB_USERNAME=postgres.[PROJECT_ID]
DB_PASSWORD=[SUPABASE_PASSWORD]
DB_SSLMODE=require

# Cache / Queue / Session (Database-driven, no Redis needed)
CACHE_STORE=database
QUEUE_CONNECTION=database
SESSION_DRIVER=database

# App Key (generate: php artisan key:generate)
APP_KEY=base64:[GENERATED_KEY]

# Mail (SendGrid for staging)
MAIL_MAILER=smtp
MAIL_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=apikey
MAIL_PASSWORD=[SENDGRID_API_KEY]
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@bayanihan-staging.gov.ph
MAIL_FROM_NAME="Bayanihan One Window (Staging)"

# Cloudinary (Staging account)
CLOUDINARY_URL=cloudinary://[API_KEY]:[API_SECRET]@[CLOUD_NAME]

# OTP Configuration
OTP_EXPIRY_MINUTES=5
OTP_DEBUG_MODE=true    # Enable debug OTP auto-fill

# IP Whitelist (comma-separated CIDR, optional)
ALLOWED_IPS=0.0.0.0/0

# AI/OpenAI (Optional, for chatbot)
OPENAI_API_KEY=[OPENAI_KEY]
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4-turbo

# Broadcast (Pusher, optional)
BROADCAST_DRIVER=log
PUSHER_APP_ID=[PUSHER_ID]
PUSHER_APP_KEY=[PUSHER_KEY]
PUSHER_APP_SECRET=[PUSHER_SECRET]
PUSHER_HOST=[PUSHER_HOST]
PUSHER_PORT=443
PUSHER_SCHEME=https

# Sanctum (API tokens)
SANCTUM_STATEFUL_DOMAINS=bayanihan-staging.onrender.com

# Logging
LOG_CHANNEL=stack
LOG_LEVEL=debug

# Session
SESSION_DRIVER=database
SESSION_LIFETIME=120
```

## Render Deploy Configuration

In Render Dashboard → Web Service Settings:

**Build Command:**
```bash
composer install --no-dev --optimize-autoloader && npm install && npm run build
```

**Start Command:**
```bash
php artisan migrate --force && php artisan db:seed --class=StagingDatabaseSeeder --force && php artisan serve --host=0.0.0.0 --port=$PORT
```

Or use Render's built-in processes:
```
npm run build
php artisan migrate --force
php artisan db:seed --class=StagingDatabaseSeeder --force
```

## Auto-Deploy on Push

In Render Dashboard → Connect GitHub:
- Repository: bayanihan/bayanihan
- Branch: main
- Auto-deploy: ON
- Auto-pull: ON (optional, pulls fresh changes)

---

## Secret Management

Use Render's Environment Variables (not committed to git):
- Database credentials
- API keys (OpenAI, SendGrid, etc.)
- Cloudinary secrets
- Pusher secrets

Store these in Render Dashboard, not in `.env.staging` in repo.

---

## Post-Deployment

After each deploy, Render runs:
1. `php artisan migrate --force` — Runs pending migrations
2. `php artisan db:seed --class=StagingDatabaseSeeder --force` — Seeds 1000+ test cases
3. App starts listening on Render's assigned port

View logs: Render Dashboard → Logs
